GOWALL(1)                      General Commands Manual

NAME
       gowall

SYNOPSIS
       gowall convert [options] path/to/img.png -t <theme-name>
       gowall convert -b [options] path/to/img1.png,path/to/img2.png -t <theme-name>
       gowall invert [options] path/to/img.png
       gowall invert -b [options] path/to/img1.png,path/to/img2.png
       gowall convert [options] ~/Pictures/# -t <theme-name>
       gowall list [options]
       gowall extract [options] /path/to/img.png -c <number>
       gowall -w

DESCRIPTION
       gowall is a tool to convert an image (specifically a wallpaper) to any color
       scheme or palette you like. It supports single and batch conversions, custom
       themes, color inversion, image previewing, and color palette extraction.

FEATURES
       - Convert single or multiple images to any supported theme.
       - Convert entire directories using the `#` delimiter.
       - Invert image colors before converting them.
       - Supports custom themes via `~/.config/gowall/config.yml`.
       - Preview images on terminal emulators like `kitty`.
       - Extract color palettes from images similar to `pywal`.

SUPPORTED FORMATS
       The following image formats are supported:

       png, jpeg, jpg, webp

USAGE
       1. Single conversion:
              gowall convert path/to/img.png -t <theme-name>

       2. Batch conversion:
              gowall convert -b path/img1.png,path/img2.png -t <theme-name>

       3. Invert colors:
              gowall invert path/to/img.png

       4. Convert a whole directory:
              gowall convert ~/Pictures/# -t <theme-name>

       5. List all theme names:
              gowall list

       6. Image previewing:
              Image previewing is on by default. Disable it in `~/.config/gowall/config.yml` by setting `EnableImagePreviewing` to `false`.

       7. Palette extraction:
              gowall extract /path/to/img.png -c <number>

       8. Wallpaper of the Day:
              gowall -w

